# A Windows checkout gets CRLF by default, and three of these files are read by
# something that does not tolerate it: /bin/sh sources docker/*.envsh inside the
# container, where a trailing \r becomes part of the command. The image would
# build fine and fail at startup with an error naming a command nobody wrote.
#
# CI is unaffected either way -- git stores LF -- so this exists entirely for
# `docker build` run from a Windows working copy.
*.envsh     text eol=lf
*.template  text eol=lf
*.sh        text eol=lf
Dockerfile  text eol=lf
